accessibility.text: multi-user security of standardized implementations of short Schnorr signatures against preprocessing attacks in ROM+GGM [New Result]
Not a compelling model for preprocessing attacks!
Usage: lower bound in Bit-Fixing Model ￼ lower bound in Auxiliary-Input Model\u2028[Coretti et al., EUROCRYPT 2018]
multi-user security of key-prefixed short Schnorr signatures against preprocessing attacks in ROM+GGM \u2028[EUROCRYPT 2022]
Proof can be difficult — we can no longer assume that RO H looks uniformly random to online attacker (due to hint)
Compression Argument: if online attacker is too successful then we can “compress” H (compressing a random string is impossible)
